 Advisors for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Independent_Institute\" title=\"The Independent Institute\">The Independent Institute<\/a>, and a Senior Fellow at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cato_Institute\" title=\"Cato Institute\">Cato Institute<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Washington_D.C.\" title=\"Washington D.C.\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Washington D.C.<\/a> In 2004 Smith was honored with an honorary doctoral degree<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vernon_L._Smith#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Universidad_Francisco_Marroqu%C3%ADn\" title=\"Universidad Francisco Marroqu\u00edn\">Universidad Francisco Marroqu\u00edn<\/a>, the institution that named the Vernon Smith Center for Experimental Economics Research after him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vernon_L._Smith#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Vernon L. Smith","place_of_birth":"Wichita, Kansas","place_of_death":null,"text":"Vernon L. Smith , Economics, 2002","year":2002.0}